sql:
SELECT name
FROM facilities
WHERE county_id = (SELECT county_id FROM counties WHERE county_name = 'Cork');

SELECT service_type_id
FROM service_logs
WHERE service_type_id = 0;

SELECT f.name AS recent_facility_name
FROM facilities f
WHERE f.last_updated = (
    SELECT MAX(last_updated)
    FROM facilities
);

external_knowledge:
- A county is an administrative region; 
- Facilities refer to healthcare or service centers in this context; 
- Patients are individuals who receive medical services or treatments; 
- Service costs represent the financial expenses associated with healthcare services; 
- Cumulative and average metrics provide a broader understanding of the distribution and central tendency of patient and cost data across counties.
